            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/component\/10073",
                    "id": 10073,
                    "name": "Zend_Locale",
                    "description": "Zend_Locale is a basic wrapper for all I18N and L10N issues for the Zend Framework. It provides the userbasically with access to translation functionality. It can handle different source file types for translation.",
                    "isAssigneeTypeValid": false
                }
            ]
        },
        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12305",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In order to avoid API problems with having a long list of optional parameters,\nwhat do you think about the following?\n{code}\nZend_Locale_Format::toNumberFormat($value, $format, $precision = false)\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-19T16:38:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-19T16:38:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12306",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No way...\n\nI can't delete the $locale parameter because without it I would not know the seperators, the standard format, the fraction seperator and the minus sign which has to be used for localized values.\n\nThe $locale parameter makes the Zend_Locale_Format::toNumberFormat function locale aware... without it the function would have no sense.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-19T17:00:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-19T17:00:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12308",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I didn't intend to leave off the $locale parameter.\nHowever, this does raise another issue and another possibility:\n\nWe could create a new class, or extend\/modify Zend_Measure_Number to support:\n\n{code}\n$numberString = new Zend_Measure_Number($input, Zend_Measure::NUMERALS, $locale)\n$numberString->setPrecision(3);\n$numberString->setLocale('de_AT');\n$numberString->toNumeralFormat($value, $format);\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-19T17:42:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-19T17:42:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12312",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Measure's useage is converting between different units and systems. This has nothing to do with the actual issue.\n\nHaving Zend_Locale_Format::toNumber();\nbeing extended to not only support the default formats but also self defined ones is a problem which has to be solved within Zend_Locale_Format... otherwise we would duplicate existing code.\n\nMyself is not seeing any problem with the first approach but a little bit different :\n\n{code}\nZend_Locale_Format::toNumberFormat($value, $format, $locale = false);\n{code}\n\nThe precission can be defined within the format and does not need an own parameter if self defined formats are used.\nThe standard formats always leave the precission as long as the original defines it. So we need $precission for the standard formats but not for the self defined ones.\n\nA format like ##,#0.# would define unlimited precission\nA format like ###0.000;-###0.0 would define a precission of 3 for positive, and 1 for negative values.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-20T16:22:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-20T16:22:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12444",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If you write the documentation and unit tests for this addition, then I would support adding this feature, after we finish all the other more important tasks for i18n components.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-29T19:44:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-29T19:44:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12453",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
